-- Kara Hobbs Joins BlueGold as Head of Marketing in London, CEO Crema Says
-- B y   C h a n y a p o r n   C h a n j a r o e n
-- 2010-09-22T01:38:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/kara-hobbs-joins-bluegold-as-head-of-marketing-in-london-ceo-crema-says.html
Kara Hobbs  has joined BlueGold
Capital Management LLP, the London-based energy hedge fund, as
head of marketing, Chief Executive Officer  Dennis Crema  said.  Hobbs, who was director of investor relations and marketing
at New York-based Ospraie Management LLC until December 2008,
started at BlueGold this month, Hobbs said yesterday from London.
Before Ospraie, Hobbs worked at Tudor Investment Corp., she said.  Hobbs replaced  Mads Hultgreen , who has moved to BNP Paribas
SA as head of commodity derivatives European hedge-fund sales,
according to an Aug. 24 statement from BNP Paribas.  To contact the reporter on this story:
